          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-4-1686317991075-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add your <strong>chicken stock mix </strong>and <strong>tomato paste </strong>with 550ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[825ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[1.1L]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Bring to the boil over a high heat</p><p>Once boiling, cover with a lid and put the dish in the oven for 25-30 min or until most of the water has absorbed and the rice and chicken is cooked (no pink meat!) – this is your <strong>one pot chicken breast paella</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/step-5-1686316931867-x200.jpg",
